title: Wheels Up Now Public, Trading On NYSE
itunes:title: Wheels Up Now Public, Trading On NYSE
description:
Kenny Dichter, Founder and CEO of Wheels Up, talks about private flight demand and the company's public debut. Nela Richardson, ADP Chief Economist, discusses the pandemic's economic impact on women in the workforce. Jason Crabtree, Co-Founder and CEO of QOMPLX, discusses ransomware protection, and the company's IPO. Sonali Basak, Bloomberg Wall Street Reporter, talks bank earnings. Hosted by Paul Sweeney and Matt Miller. (Taylor Riggs fills in for Matt Miller)

See omnystudio.com/listener for privacy information.
